{"title_page": "West Village, Dallas", "text_new": "{{Advert|date=January 2012}}\n[[File:West Village Dallas.jpg|thumb|West Village]]\n[[File:West Village Dallas 3.jpg|thumb|West Village Dallas]]\n[[File:West Village Dallas 2.jpg|thumb|West Village Dallas]]\n[[File:West Village Dallas 1.jpg|thumb|West Village Dallas]]\n\nThe '''West Village District''' is a walkable urban village in the [[Uptown Dallas|Uptown]] area of [[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]], [[Texas]]. West Village is located at the northern edge of Uptown along McKinney Avenue and is bordered by Lemmon Avenue, Cole Avenue, Haskell Drive and [[Central Expressway (Dallas)|Central Expressway]]. West Village proper has 88 retail, restaurant and entertainment tenants within {{convert|244000|sqft|m2}} and contains approximately 700 residential units.<ref>http://www.westvil.com/</ref> This has been the catalyst for the West Village District, which contains approximately 3,600 residential units, an emerging office market (including the Richard's Group Corporate Headquarters), and an estimated 500,000 square feet of gross leasable space- all within walking distance.\n\n==History==\nWest Village, opened in 2001, was built on an undeveloped assembly that was cleared in the 1980s for a large, master-planned urban community to be known as CityPlace. West Village was developed by Urban Partners, Henry S. Miller Interests, Phoenix Property Company, and The CityPlace Company. The original development, designed by Washington architect [[David M. Schwarz]], is a [[mixed-use development]] with the retail portion managed by Urban Partners and the residential component managed by CIM. The name West Village is completely made up and is an attempt to link the development to the urban neighborhood in New York City. Over subsequent years the development has continued to stimulate further development as thousands of urban apartment homes have been constructed in the immediate vicinity.\n\n==Transportation==\nWest Village is two miles (1.6&nbsp;km) north of [[Downtown Dallas]]. The DART {{DART R|style=nl}} and {{DART B|style=nl}} light rail lines stop at the Uptown/CityPlace station (located within the West Village District). The [[McKinney Avenue Transit Authority]]'s M-line streetcar travels from [[downtown Dallas]] to Cityplace Station and loops around the West Village.\n\nThe [[Katy Trail (Dallas)|Katy Trail]], a noted Dallas running and biking corridor, is within a block of the development.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Dallas Neighborhoods|selected=oaklawn}}\n{{Uptown, Dallas}}\n{{Dallas}}\n{{Dallas malls}}\n\n{{coord missing|Texas}}\n\n[[Category:Transit-oriented developments in the United States]]\n[[Category:New Classical architecture]]\n[[Category:David M. Schwarz buildings]]\n", "text_old": "{{Advert|date=January 2012}}\n[[File:West Village Dallas.jpg|thumb|West Village]]\n[[File:West Village Dallas 3.jpg|thumb|West Village Dallas]]\n[[File:West Village Dallas 2.jpg|thumb|West Village Dallas]]\n[[File:West Village Dallas 1.jpg|thumb|West Village Dallas]]\n\nThe '''West Village District''' is a walkable urban village in the [[Uptown Dallas|Uptown]] area of [[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]], [[Texas]]. West Village is located at the northern edge of Uptown along McKinney Avenue and is bordered by Lemmon Avenue, Cole Avenue, Haskell Drive and [[Central Expressway (Dallas)|Central Expressway]]. West Village proper has 88 retail, restaurant and entertainment tenants within {{convert|244000|sqft|m2}} and contains approximately 700 residential units.<ref>http://www.westvil.com/</ref> This has been the catalyst for the West Village District, which contains approximately 3,600 residential units, an emerging office market (including the Richard's Group Corporate Headquarters), and an estimated 500,000 square feet of gross leasable space- all within walking distance.\n\n==History==\nWest Village, opened in 2001, was built on an undeveloped assembly that was cleared in the 1980s for a large, master-planned urban community to be known as CityPlace. West Village was developed by Urban Partners, Henry S. Miller Interests, Phoenix Property Company, and The CityPlace Company. The original development, designed by Washington architect [[David M. Schwarz]], is a [[mixed-use development]] with the retail portion managed by Urban Partners and the residential component managed by CIM. The name West Village is completely made up and is an attempt to link the development to the urban neighborhood in New York City. Over subsequent years the development has continued to stimulate further development as thousands of urban apartment homes have been constructed in the immediate vicinity.\n\n==Transportation==\nWest Village is two miles (1.6&nbsp;km) north of [[Downtown Dallas]]. The DART {{DART R|style=nl}} and {{DART B|style=nl}} light rail lines stop at the Uptown/CityPlace station (located within the West Village District). The [[McKinney Avenue Transit Authority]]'s M-line streetcar travels from [[downtown Dallas]] to Cityplace Station and loops around the West Village.\n\nThe [[Katy Trail (Dallas)|Katy Trail]], a noted Dallas running and biking corridor, is within a block of the development.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Dallas Neighborhoods|selected=oaklawn}}\n{{Uptown, Dallas}}\n{{Dallas}}\n{{Dallas malls}}\n\n{{coord missing|Texas}}\n\n[[Category:Transit-oriented developments in the United States]]\n[[Category:New Classical architecture]]\n", "name_user": "Herrikez", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Village,_Dallas"}
{"title_page": "I Am Not a Dog on a Chain", "text_new": "{{use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = I Am Not a Dog on a Chain\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Morrissey]]\n| cover      = Morrissey - I Am Not a Dog on a Chain.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|2020|03|20|df=y}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     = {{flatlist|\n* Studio La Fabrique, [[Saint-R\u00e9my-de-Provence]], France\n* [[The Sound Factory|Sunset Sound]], Hollywood}}\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 49:30\n| label      = [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]\n| producer   = [[Joe Chiccarelli]]\n| prev_title = [[California Son]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n| name        = I Am Not a Dog on a Chain\n| type        = studio\n| single1     = Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\n| single1date = 10 January 2020\n| single2     = Love Is On Its Way Out\n| single2date = 31 January 2020\n| single3     = Knockabout World\n| single3date = 21 February 2020\n}}}}\n'''''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain''''' is the thirteenth studio album by [[Morrissey]], released through [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]] on 20 March 2020. It is Morrissey's first album of original material since 2017's ''[[Low in High School]]''.<ref name=\"CoS\">{{cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/11/morrissey-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain/|title=Morrissey announces new album I Am Not a Dog on a Chain|website=[[Consequence of Sound]]|first=Alex|last=Young|date=28 November 2019|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref> It was produced by [[Joe Chiccarelli]], and lead single \"Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\" features vocals from [[Thelma Houston]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/morrissey-announces-new-album-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-shares-song/|title=Morrissey Announces New Album ''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain'', Shares Song|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last1=Bloom|first1=Madison|last2=Monroe|first2=Jazz|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nIn a statement, Morrissey called the album \"the very best of me\" and \"too good to be true [...] too true to be considered good\".<ref name=\"CoS\"/> Producer [[Joe Chiccarelli]] described it as Morrissey's \"boldest and most adventurous album yet\", claiming that he has \"pushed the boundaries yet again \u2013 both musically and lyrically\".<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-announces-new-album-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-2579954|title=Morrissey announces new album 'I Am Not A Dog on a Chain'|work=[[NME]]|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=11 January 2020|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe album was produced by Joe Chiccarelli and recorded at Studio La Fabrique in [[Saint-R\u00e9my-de-Provence]], France, as well as [[The Sound Factory|Sunset Sound]] in [[Hollywood]].<ref name=\"NME\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/morrissey-new-album-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-919750/|title=Morrissey Announces New Album 'I Am Not a Dog on a Chain'|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 64/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain/morrissey|title=I Am Not a Dog on a Chain by Morrissey|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev1score = B\u2212<ref name=\"AVC\">{{Cite web|url=https://music.avclub.com/morrissey-barks-and-bites-on-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-1842399465|title=Morrissey Barks and Bites on ''I Am Not a Dog On a Chain''|website=[[The A.V. Club]]|last=Modell|first=Josh|date=20 March 2020|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev2score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-mw0003348802|title=''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain''&nbsp;\u2013 Morrissey|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|author-link=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/mar/20/morrissey-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-review|title=Morrissey: I Am Not a Dog on a Chain review \u2013 old man yells at cloud|work=[[The Guardian]]|last=Snapes|first=Laura|date=20 March 2020|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/morrissey-review-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-tracklist-the-smiths-stream-a9413416.html|title=Morrissey review, I am Not a Dog on a Chain: All bark and no bite|work=[[The Independent]]|last=Cudsi|first=Jake|date=20 March 2020|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev5score = 6.1/10<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/morrissey-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain/|title=Morrissey: I Am Not a Dog On a Chain Album Review|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Tavakoli|first=Mina|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/what-to-listen-to/morrissey-not-dog-chain-review-great-anything-has-ever-written/|title=Morrissey, I Am Not a Dog on a Chain, review: as great as anything he has ever written|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|last=McCormick|first= Neil|date=14 March 2020|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain'' currently holds a score of 64 out of 100 on review aggregator [[Metacritic]] based on eight reviews.<ref name=\"MC\"/> Josh Modell of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' gave the album a B\u2212 and felt that the lyrical content was the weakest but that Morrissey displayed songcraft and \"a great vocal performance\".<ref name=\"AVC\"/> The editorial staff of [[AllMusic]] gave the album 3.5 out of five stars, with reviewer [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] summing up his review by calling the album \"one of the better latter-day Morrissey records\" but decrying how \"placid and complacent he's been for the better part of a decade\".<ref name=\"AM\"/> Mina Tavakoli of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' rated the album 6.1 out of 10 and called it \"frequently ridiculous, mildly captivating, and occasionally repetitive, pocked by moments of goofiness that come from the runoff of a man eager to chase old miseries and find new ones to berate\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/>\n\nWriting for ''[[The Independent]]'', Jake Cudsi rated the album two out of five stars, opining that it \"has its moments, but they are brief and virtually lost amid the more experimental forays\".<ref name=\"Independent\"/> Laura Snapes of ''[[The Guardian]]'' also gave the album two out of five stars, judging that Morrissey plays the \"victim\" and is \"often lost among the strident music as he hectors people afraid to be themselves\", although his \"coyness undermines his apparent glee as a truth-teller\".<ref name=\"Guardian\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Jim Jim Falls\n| writer1 = Morrissey, [[Jesse Tobias]]\n| length1 = 3:44\n| title2 = Love Is on Its Way Out\n| writer2 = Morrissey, [[Gustavo Manzur]]\n| length2 = 3:15\n| title3 = Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\n| writer3 = Morrissey, Manzur\n| length3 = 5:46\n| title4 = I Am Not a Dog on a Chain\n| writer4 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length4 = 3:53\n| title5 = What Kind of People Live in These Houses?\n| writer5 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length5 = 3:42\n| title6 = Knockabout World\n| writer6 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length6 = 3:25\n| title7 = Darling, I Hug a Pillow\n| writer7 = Morrissey, Mando Lopez\n| length7 = 4:47\n| title8 = Once I Saw the River Clean\n| writer8 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length8 = 4:20\n| title9 = The Truth About Ruth\n| writer9 = Morrissey, Manzur\n| length9 = 3:45\n| title10 = The Secret of Music\n| writer10 = Morrissey, Lopez\n| length10 = 7:52\n| title11 = My Hurling Days Are Done\n| writer11 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length11 = 5:01\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Morrissey]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n*[[Boz Boorer]]&nbsp;\u2013 clarinet, acoustic and electric guitar, mandolin, saxophone, string arrangements, [[zither]]\n*Andrea Bulletti&nbsp;\u2013 electric guitar, slide guitar, drum programming, keys on \u201cThe Secret of Music\u201d\n*[[Joe Chiccarelli]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Record producer|production]], drum [[Programming (music)|programming]], [[Audio engineer|engineering]], synthesizer\n*Daniel Cayotte&nbsp;\u2013 recitation\n*Sally Chae&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals\n*Mike Daly&nbsp;\u2013 drum programming, synthesizer\n*Glendale Tab & Apple Choir&nbsp;\u2013 vocals\n*[[Thelma Houston]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals on \"Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\"\n*Sean Hurley&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n*Victor Indrizzo&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n*[[Greg Leisz]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[pedal steel guitar]]\n*Danny Levin&nbsp;\u2013 trumpet\n*Mando Lopez&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n*[[Roger Joseph Manning Jr.|Roger Manning]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[harmonium]], horn, [[Mellotron]], organ, piano, string arrangements, synthesizer, backing vocals\n*Gustavo Manzur&nbsp;\u2013 accordion, drum programming, [[nylon string guitar]], Mellotron, piano, synthesizer, backing vocals\n*Karla Manzur&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals\n*Rose Mary&nbsp;\u2013 laughing\n*David Ralicke&nbsp;\u2013 saxophone\n*Bridget Regan&nbsp;\u2013 fiddle\n*Ken Sluiter&nbsp;\u2013 mixing\n*Megan Sluiter&nbsp;\u2013 laughing\n*[[Jesse Tobias]]&nbsp;\u2013 acoustic and electric guitars, recitation, [[electric sitar]]\n*[[Matt Walker (drummer)|Matt Walker]]&nbsp;\u2013 drums, percussion \n\n'''Technical personnel'''\n*John Fekner&nbsp;\u2013 photography\n*Miro La Gagioia&nbsp;\u2013 assistant engineering\n*Liam Lynch&nbsp;\u2013 artwork, design\n*Chris Stewart&nbsp;\u2013 cover photo\n*Jose Vergara&nbsp;\u2013 photography\n*Emily Lazar&nbsp;\u2013 mastering engineering\n*Chris Allgood&nbsp;\u2013 assistant mastering engineering\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Austria|32|artist=Morrissey|album=I Am Not a Dog on a Chain|rowheader=true|accessdate=2 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|80|artist=Morrissey|album=I Am Not a Dog on a Chain|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|80|artist=Morrissey|album=I Am Not a Dog on a Chain|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|13|id=404345|artist=Morrissey|album=I Am Not a Dog on a Chain|rowheader=true|accessdate=27 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland3|47|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italian Albums ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fimi.it/top-of-the-music/classifiche.kl#/charts/1/2020/13|title=Album \u2013 Classifica settimanale WK 13 (dal 20.3.2020 al 26.3.2020)|publisher=[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana]]|language=Italian|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 89\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|1|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Spanish Albums ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/4348-%C3%81lbumes-semana-13-2020|title=Top 100 Albumes \u2013 Semana 13: del 20.3.2020 al 26.3.2020|publisher=[[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|56|artist=Morrissey|album=I Am Not a Dog on a Chain|rowheader=true|accessdate=1 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK2|3|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UKIndependent|1|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=30 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardIndependent|44|artist=Morrissey|rowheader=true|accessdate=1 April 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Discogs master|1700539}}\n*{{Musicbrainz release group|602d4071-2abc-4a94-9e1b-0a8dcba94561}}\n\n{{Morrissey}}\n\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Joe Chiccarelli]]\n[[Category:BMG albums]]\n[[Category:Morrissey albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = I Am Not a Dog on a Chain\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Morrissey]]\n| cover      = Morrissey - I Am Not a Dog on a Chain.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|2020|03|20|df=y}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     = {{flatlist|\n* Studio La Fabrique, [[Saint-R\u00e9my-de-Provence]], France\n* [[The Sound Factory|Sunset Sound]], Hollywood}}\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 49:30\n| label      = [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]\n| producer   = [[Joe Chiccarelli]]\n| prev_title = [[California Son]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n| name        = I Am Not a Dog on a Chain\n| type        = studio\n| single1     = Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\n| single1date = 10 January 2020\n| single2     = Love Is On Its Way Out\n| single2date = 31 January 2020\n| single3     = Knockabout World\n| single3date = 21 February 2020\n}}}}\n'''''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain''''' is the thirteenth studio album by [[Morrissey]], released through [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]] on 20 March 2020. It is Morrissey's first album of original material since 2017's ''[[Low in High School]]''.<ref name=\"CoS\">{{cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/11/morrissey-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain/|title=Morrissey announces new album I Am Not a Dog on a Chain|website=[[Consequence of Sound]]|first=Alex|last=Young|date=28 November 2019|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref> It was produced by [[Joe Chiccarelli]], and lead single \"Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\" features vocals from [[Thelma Houston]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/morrissey-announces-new-album-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-shares-song/|title=Morrissey Announces New Album ''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain'', Shares Song|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last1=Bloom|first1=Madison|last2=Monroe|first2=Jazz|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nIn a statement, Morrissey called the album \"the very best of me\" and \"too good to be true [...] too true to be considered good\".<ref name=\"CoS\"/> Producer [[Joe Chiccarelli]] described it as Morrissey's \"boldest and most adventurous album yet\", claiming that he has \"pushed the boundaries yet again \u2013 both musically and lyrically\".<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-announces-new-album-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-2579954|title=Morrissey announces new album 'I Am Not A Dog on a Chain'|work=[[NME]]|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=11 January 2020|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe album was produced by Joe Chiccarelli and recorded at Studio La Fabrique in [[Saint-R\u00e9my-de-Provence]], France, as well as [[The Sound Factory|Sunset Sound]] in [[Hollywood]].<ref name=\"NME\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/morrissey-new-album-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-919750/|title=Morrissey Announces New Album 'I Am Not a Dog on a Chain'|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 64/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain/morrissey|title=I Am Not a Dog on a Chain by Morrissey|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev1score = B\u2212<ref name=\"AVC\">{{Cite web|url=https://music.avclub.com/morrissey-barks-and-bites-on-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-1842399465|title=Morrissey Barks and Bites on ''I Am Not a Dog On a Chain''|website=[[The A.V. Club]]|last=Modell|first=Josh|date=20 March 2020|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev2score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-mw0003348802|title=''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain''&nbsp;\u2013 Morrissey|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|author-link=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/mar/20/morrissey-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-review|title=Morrissey: I Am Not a Dog on a Chain review \u2013 old man yells at cloud|work=[[The Guardian]]|last=Snapes|first=Laura|date=20 March 2020|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/morrissey-review-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-tracklist-the-smiths-stream-a9413416.html|title=Morrissey review, I am Not a Dog on a Chain: All bark and no bite|work=[[The Independent]]|last=Cudsi|first=Jake|date=20 March 2020|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev5score = 6.1/10<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/morrissey-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain/|title=Morrissey: I Am Not a Dog On a Chain Album Review|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Tavakoli|first=Mina|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/what-to-listen-to/morrissey-not-dog-chain-review-great-anything-has-ever-written/|title=Morrissey, I Am Not a Dog on a Chain, review: as great as anything he has ever written|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|last=McCormick|first= Neil|date=14 March 2020|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n''I Am Not a Dog on a Chain'' currently holds a score of 64 out of 100 on review aggregator [[Metacritic]] based on eight reviews.<ref name=\"MC\"/> Josh Modell of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' gave the album a B\u2212 and felt that the lyrical content was the weakest but that Morrissey displayed songcraft and \"a great vocal performance\".<ref name=\"AVC\"/> The editorial staff of [[AllMusic]] gave the album 3.5 out of five stars, with reviewer [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] summing up his review by calling the album \"one of the better latter-day Morrissey records\" but decrying how \"placid and complacent he's been for the better part of a decade\".<ref name=\"AM\"/> Mina Tavakoli of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' rated the album 6.1 out of 10 and called it \"frequently ridiculous, mildly captivating, and occasionally repetitive, pocked by moments of goofiness that come from the runoff of a man eager to chase old miseries and find new ones to berate\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/>\n\nWriting for ''[[The Independent]]'', Jake Cudsi rated the album two out of five stars, opining that it \"has its moments, but they are brief and virtually lost amid the more experimental forays\".<ref name=\"Independent\"/> Laura Snapes of ''[[The Guardian]]'' also gave the album two out of five stars, judging that Morrissey plays the \"victim\" and is \"often lost among the strident music as he hectors people afraid to be themselves\", although his \"coyness undermines his apparent glee as a truth-teller\".<ref name=\"Guardian\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Jim Jim Falls\n| writer1 = Morrissey, [[Jesse Tobias]]\n| length1 = 3:44\n| title2 = Love Is on Its Way Out\n| writer2 = Morrissey, [[Gustavo Manzur]]\n| length2 = 3:15\n| title3 = Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\n| writer3 = Morrissey, Manzur\n| length3 = 5:46\n| title4 = I Am Not a Dog on a Chain\n| writer4 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length4 = 3:53\n| title5 = What Kind of People Live in These Houses?\n| writer5 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length5 = 3:42\n| title6 = Knockabout World\n| writer6 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length6 = 3:25\n| title7 = Darling, I Hug a Pillow\n| writer7 = Morrissey, Mando Lopez\n| length7 = 4:47\n| title8 = Once I Saw the River Clean\n| writer8 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length8 = 4:20\n| title9 = The Truth About Ruth\n| writer9 = Morrissey, Manzur\n| length9 = 3:45\n| title10 = The Secret of Music\n| writer10 = Morrissey, Lopez\n| length10 = 7:52\n| title11 = My Hurling Days Are Done\n| writer11 = Morrissey, Tobias\n| length11 = 5:01\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Morrissey]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n*[[Boz Boorer]]&nbsp;\u2013 clarinet, acoustic and electric guitar, mandolin, saxophone, string arrangements, [[zither]]\n*Andrea Bulletti&nbsp;\u2013 electric guitar, slide guitar, drum programming, keys on \u201cThe Secret of Music\u201d\n*[[Joe Chiccarelli]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Record producer|production]], drum [[Programming (music)|programming]], [[Audio engineer|engineering]], synthesizer\n*Daniel Cayotte&nbsp;\u2013 recitation\n*Sally Chae&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals\n*Mike Daly&nbsp;\u2013 drum programming, synthesizer\n*Glendale Tab & Apple Choir&nbsp;\u2013 vocals\n*[[Thelma Houston]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals on \"Bobby, Don't You Think They Know?\"\n*Sean Hurley&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n*Victor Indrizzo&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n*[[Greg Leisz]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[pedal steel guitar]]\n*Danny Levin&nbsp;\u2013 trumpet\n*Mando Lopez&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n*[[Roger Joseph Manning Jr.|Roger Manning]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[harmonium]], horn, [[Mellotron]], organ, piano, string arrangements, synthesizer, backing vocals\n*Gustavo Manzur&nbsp;\u2013 accordion, drum programming, [[nylon string guitar]], Mellotron, piano, synthesizer, backing vocals\n*Karla Manzur&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals\n*Rose Mary&nbsp;\u2