Parliament constituency)|Leeds South]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|14 December 1955<br /><small>''([[1955 Labour Party leadership election|elected]])''</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\"|18 January 1963<br /><small>''(died in office)''</small>\n| height=50 style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}; border-bottom:solid 0 gray; border-top:solid 0 gray\" |\n|-\n| height=50 style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}; border-bottom:solid 0 gray\" |\n! style=\"font-weight:normal\" rowspan=\"3\"|[[Harold Macmillan|Macmillan]] <small>{{nowrap|1957\u20131963}}</small>\n|-\n| [[George Brown, Baron George-Brown|George Brown]]{{efn|name=Acting}}<br /><small>(1914\u20131985)</small>\n| [[File:George Brown, 1967.jpg|60px]]\n| [[Belper (UK Parliament constituency)|Belper]]\n| 18 January 1963\n| 14 February 1963\n| height=50 style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}; border-bottom:solid 0 gray; border-top:solid 0 gray\" |\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|[[Harold Wilson]]<br /><small>(1916\u20131995)</small>\n| rowspan=\"5\"|[[File:Dodwilson.JPG|center|60px]]\n| rowspan=\"5\"|[[Huyton (UK Parliament constituency)|Huyton]]\n| rowspan=\"5\"|14 February 1963<br /><small>''([[1963 Labour Party leadership election (UK)|elected]])''</small>\n| rowspan=\"5\"|5 April 1976\n| height=20 style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}; border-top:solid 0 gray\" |\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n! style=\"font-weight:normal\"|[[Alec Douglas-Home|Douglas-Home]] <small>{{nowrap|1963\u20131964}}</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| ''himself'' {{small|1964\u20131970}}\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n! style=\"font-weight:normal\"|[[Edward Heath|Heath]] <small>{{nowrap|1970\u20131974}}</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| ''himself'' {{small|1974\u20131976}}\n|-\n| rowspa